ngthening regulatory effectiveness. Simplification ensures that only truly necessary data is collected, minimizing unnecessary reporting. Harmonization reduces unique compliance burdens by aligning with broader industry standards where appropriate, fostering consistency across the financial sector. Modernization leverages technology to streamline reporting processes, benefiting both the agency and the regulated entities by improving data quality and reducing administrative overhead. These recommendations directly address the Paperwork Reduction Act's goals of minimizing burden and maximizing the practical utility of information collections, as well as the general call for public comments within the notice itself."
